com.cyc.baseclient.kbtool

Class CycUnassertTool

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.baseclient.AbstractKBTool
      • com.cyc.baseclient.kbtool.CycUnassertTool
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    UnassertTool

    public class CycUnassertTool
extends AbstractKBTool
implements UnassertTool
    Tools for unasserting facts from the Cyc KB. To assert facts to the Cyc KB, use the CycAssertTool. To perform simple tasks, like renaming constants, use the CycObjectTool.
    See Also:
    CycAssertTool, CycObjectTool

      • killWithoutTranscript

        public void killWithoutTranscript(CycConstant cycConstant)
                           throws CycConnectionException,
                                  CycApiException
        Kills a Cyc constant without issuing a transcript operation. If CYCCONSTANT is a microtheory, then all the contained assertions are deleted from the KB, the Cyc Truth Maintenance System (TMS) will automatically delete any derived assertions whose sole support is the killed term(s).
        Specified by:
        killWithoutTranscript in interface UnassertTool
        Parameters:
        cycConstant - the constant term to be removed from the KB
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException - if a communications error occurs
        CycApiException - if the api request results in a cyc server error

                             boolean bookkeeping,

        Deprecated. 
        Forcefully Unasserts the given assertion. See attendant warnings on UnassertTool.blastAssertion(com.cyc.base.cycobject.CycAssertion, boolean, boolean). If done within the context of a transaction, the blast will be performed immediately, and will not be done in the context of the transaction.
